properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued February 7 at 5:01AM AKST until February 7 at 8:00AM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Juneau has issued a Dense Fog
Advisory, which is in effect until 8 AM AKST this morning.

* LOCATION...Ketchikan.

* VISIBILITY...One quarter mile.

* TIMING...Low clouds and visibility will improve through the
morning as winds turn out of the north.

* IMPACTS...Travel will be hazardous due to reduced visibility.
Low clouds will keep hill side areas in the fog the longest.
Temperatures below freezing may result in black ice.
properties.instruction:
An advisory means that dense fog is already occurring or
imminent.

All travel should be done with extreme caution.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM AKST THIS MORNING
